OL,3,CHow one school is bucking attendance
OL,4,Ctrends
OL,6,FThe average school attendance rate for
OL,7,FWales currently stands at 91.8% for
OL,8,Fthis academic year. Within this
OL,9,Ffigure, 7.0% of pupils eligible for
OL,10,FFree School Meals were persistently
OL,11,Fabsent.
OL,13,FWhile there are a range of reasons or
OL,14,Funderlying causes for learner absence,
OL,15,Feffective relationships between
OL,16,Fschools and parents are considered
OL,17,Fpivotal in helping children re-engage
OL,18,Fwith school. The Welsh Government has
OL,19,Finvested #7 million this year to help
OL,20,Fsupport this.
